
[1]compendious

   COMPENDIOUS, a.

   1. Short; summary; abridged; comprehensive; containing the substance or
   general principles of a subject or work in a narrow compas; as a
   compendious system of chimistry; a compendious grammar.

   2. Short; direct; near; not circuitous; as a compendious way to acquire
   science.
